    desc="Mana Type: Sand"
    status="DRAFT"
><>

<title>Sand Mana<>

<content>
    <section> Introduction <>
        <p>Sand mana is a type of mana which is harvested from the fine sand of deserts and beaches.<>
        <p>Sand mana has an affinity with <a t="#mana_*_stone">#<> and <a t="#mana_*_glass">#<>.<>

    <section> Archetypes <>
        <heading level="1">Sand Manipulator<>
        <p>Sand <a t="#mana_*_manipulators">manipulators<> throw about clouds of sand to hinder and scratch at
        their enemies.<>
        <p>In the presence of sand, sand manipulators can manipulate far greater amounts of sand.<>

        <heading level="1">Sand Armorers<>
        <p>Sand <a t="#mana_*_armorers">armorers<> cover themselves in a cloud of flowing sand making them hard to see
        and hard to hit.<>
        <p>In the presence of sand, sand armorers can create significantly vaster clouds of armor.<>

        <heading level="1">Sand Animators<>
        <p>Sand <a t="#mana_*_animators">animators<> can create sand elementals to do their bidding. Sand elementals
        cannot hit hard, but are difficult to hit and can hinder enemies very effectively.<>
        <p>In the presence of sand, sand casters can manipulate flames as well as emitting their own attacks.<>

        <heading level="1">Sand Item Wielders<>
        <p>Sand <a t="#mana_*_itemWielders">item wielders<> wield items that emit sand clouds upon use.
        Examples include sand cloaks and sand bombs.<>
<>
